cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "closure: an open research program on inference-time structure in LLMs"
message: "If you use or refer to this program, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "closure research program contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/data-mission/closure"
abstract: >-
  A pre-registered open research program testing whether structural
  quality measurements of language-model output (grounding, rigidity,
  preserved ambiguity, and related contracts) are independent tests or
  noisy readouts of one latent property ("closure"). Eight experiments,
  each with pre-registered verdict conditions, a living hypothesis
  registry, and a citation-verification ledger.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - evaluation
  - hallucination
  - factor analysis
  - pre-registration
  - reproducibility
license: MIT
